hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.5) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added automatic creation of /etc/uuid file with 128-bit UUID for system identification
  * UUID file is created early in the configuration process if it doesn't exist
  * Existing UUID files are preserved to maintain system identity across updates
  * Added Python uuid module dependency for UUID generation

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 04 Jul 2025 12:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.4) stable; urgency=medium

  * Moved configuration files to /etc/hifiberry/baseconfig/ for better organization
  * Updated default paths for services.conf, configfiles.conf, and command.conf
  * Updated man page documentation to reflect new file locations

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 03 Jul 2025 15:45:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.3) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added command.conf support for executing commands during base configuration
  * Added configure-webui setup command to automatically configure web UI nginx integration
  * Added --commands-conf, --commands-only command line arguments
  * Enhanced error handling and logging for command execution

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 03 Jul 2025 15:30:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.2) stable; urgency=medium

  * Removed automatic baseconfig execution during package installation
  * Users must now manually run 'sudo baseconfig' or 'sudo hifiberry-baseconfig'
  * Added informational message in postinst about manual configuration

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 03 Jul 2025 15:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Renamed base-config script to hifiberry-baseconfig for consistency
  * Updated package installation to include hifiberry-baseconfig binary
  * Added corresponding man page hifiberry-baseconfig(8)
  * Maintained backward compatibility with existing baseconfig script

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 03 Jul 2025 14:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added base-config script for comprehensive system configuration
  * Automatic systemd service management from services.conf
  * Configuration file overwrite management from configfiles.conf
  * Added --force option to skip confirmation prompts
  * Added volume-restore service to default enabled services
  * Comprehensive command-line options for selective processing
  * Added man page documentation for base-config command
  * Configuration files installed to /etc/hifiberry/

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 03 Jul 2025 12:00:00 +0000

hifiberry-baseconfig (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release
  * Base configuration script for HiFiBerry OS
  * Generates system UUID if missing

